events.description: Twelfth Council of Toledo: King Erwig of the Visigoths initiates a council in which he implements diverse measures against the Jews in Spain.
events.html: • 681 – Twelfth Council of Toledo: King Erwig of the Visigoths initiates a council in which he implements diverse measures against the Jews in Spain.[1]

events.description: Jin–Song Wars: Invading Jurchen soldiers from the Jin dynasty besiege and sack Bianjing (Kaifeng), the capital of the Song dynasty of China, and abduct Emperor Qinzong of Song and others, ending the Northern Song dynasty.
events.html: • 1127 – Jin–Song Wars: Invading Jurchen soldiers from the Jin dynasty besiege and sack Bianjing (Kaifeng), the capital of the Song dynasty of China, and abduct Emperor Qinzong of Song and others, ending the Northern Song dynasty.[2]

events.description: The Jewish population of Basel, believed by the residents to be the cause of the ongoing Black Death, is rounded up and incinerated.
events.html: • 1349 – The Jewish population of Basel, believed by the residents to be the cause of the ongoing Black Death, is rounded up and incinerated.[3]

events.description: The trial of Joan of Arc begins in Rouen.
events.html: • 1431 – The trial of Joan of Arc begins in Rouen.[4]

events.description: Sicily earthquake: The first of two earthquakes destroys parts of Sicily and Malta. After the second quake on 11 January, the death toll is estimated at between 60,000 and 100,000 people.
events.html: • 1693 – Sicily earthquake: The first of two earthquakes destroys parts of Sicily and Malta. After the second quake on 11 January, the death toll is estimated at between 60,000 and 100,000 people.[5]

events.description: Ahmad Shah Durrani defeats the Marathas in the Battle of Barari Ghat.
events.html: • 1760 – Ahmad Shah Durrani defeats the Marathas in the Battle of Barari Ghat.[6]

entities.name: Indian Campaign of Ahmad Shah Durrani

events.description: The nationally known image of the Black Nazarene in the Philippines was transferred from what is now Rizal Park to its present shrine in the minor basilica of Quiapo Church. This is annually commemorated through its Traslación (solemn transfer) in the streets of Manila and is attended by millions of devotees.
events.html: • 1787 – The nationally known image of the Black Nazarene in the Philippines was transferred from what is now Rizal Park to its present shrine in the minor basilica of Quiapo Church. This is annually commemorated through its Traslación (solemn transfer) in the streets of Manila and is attended by millions of devotees.[7][8][9]

events.description: Connecticut becomes the fifth state to ratify the United States Constitution.
events.html: • 1788 – Connecticut becomes the fifth state to ratify the United States Constitution.[10]

events.description: Treaty of Jassy between Russian and Ottoman Empire is signed, ending the Russo-Turkish War of 1787–92.
events.html: • 1792 – Treaty of Jassy between Russian and Ottoman Empire is signed, ending the Russo-Turkish War of 1787–92.[11]

events.description: Jean-Pierre Blanchard becomes the first person to fly in a balloon in the United States.
events.html: • 1793 – Jean-Pierre Blanchard becomes the first person to fly in a balloon in the United States.[12]

events.description: British Prime Minister William Pitt the Younger introduces an income tax of two shillings to the pound to raise funds for Great Britain's war effort in the Napoleonic Wars.
events.html: • 1799 – British Prime Minister William Pitt the Younger introduces an income tax of two shillings to the pound to raise funds for Great Britain's war effort in the Napoleonic Wars.[13]

entities.name: Prime Minister of the United Kingdom

events.description: Admiral Horatio Lord Nelson receives a state funeral and is interred in St Paul's Cathedral.
events.html: • 1806 – Admiral Horatio Lord Nelson receives a state funeral and is interred in St Paul's Cathedral.[14]

events.description: Humphry Davy tests his safety lamp for miners at Hebburn Colliery.
events.html: • 1816 – Humphry Davy tests his safety lamp for miners at Hebburn Colliery.[15]

events.description: The Portuguese prince Pedro I of Brazil decides to stay in Brazil against the orders of the Portuguese King João VI, beginning the Brazilian independence process.
events.html: • 1822 – The Portuguese prince Pedro I of Brazil decides to stay in Brazil against the orders of the Portuguese King João VI, beginning the Brazilian independence process.[16]

events.description: The French Academy of Sciences announces the Daguerreotype photography process.
events.html: • 1839 – The French Academy of Sciences announces the Daguerreotype photography process.[17]

events.description: The 7.9 Mw  Fort Tejon earthquake shakes Central and Southern California with a maximum Mercalli intensity of IX (Violent).
events.html: • 1857 – The 7.9 Mw  Fort Tejon earthquake shakes Central and Southern California with a maximum Mercalli intensity of IX (Violent).[18]

events.description: British forces finally defeat Rajab Ali Khan of Chittagong
events.html: • 1858 – British forces finally defeat Rajab Ali Khan of Chittagong[19]

events.description: American Civil War: "Star of the West" incident occurs near Charleston, South Carolina.
events.html: • 1861 – American Civil War: "Star of the West" incident occurs near Charleston, South Carolina.[20]

events.description: Mississippi becomes the second state to secede from the Union before the outbreak of the American Civil War.
events.html: • 1861 – Mississippi becomes the second state to secede from the Union before the outbreak of the American Civil War.[21]

entities.name: Mississippi in the American Civil War

events.description: Umberto I becomes King of Italy.
events.html: • 1878 – Umberto I becomes King of Italy.[22]

events.description: Hallam Tennyson, 2nd Baron Tennyson, son of the poet Alfred Tennyson, becomes the second Governor-General of Australia.
events.html: • 1903 – Hallam Tennyson, 2nd Baron Tennyson, son of the poet Alfred Tennyson, becomes the second Governor-General of Australia.[23]

events.description: Ernest Shackleton, leading the Nimrod Expedition to the South Pole, plants the British flag 97 nautical miles (180 km; 112 mi) from the South Pole, the farthest anyone had ever reached at that time.
events.html: • 1909 – Ernest Shackleton, leading the Nimrod Expedition to the South Pole, plants the British flag 97 nautical miles (180 km; 112 mi) from the South Pole, the farthest anyone had ever reached at that time.

events.description: The Phi Beta Sigma fraternity is founded by African-American students at Howard University in Washington D.C., United States.
events.html: • 1914 – The Phi Beta Sigma fraternity is founded by African-American students at Howard University in Washington D.C., United States.[24]

events.description: World War I: The Battle of Gallipoli concludes with an Ottoman Empire victory when the last Allied forces are evacuated from the peninsula.
events.html: • 1916 – World War I: The Battle of Gallipoli concludes with an Ottoman Empire victory when the last Allied forces are evacuated from the peninsula.[25]

events.description: World War I: The Battle of Rafa is fought near the Egyptian border with Palestine.
events.html: • 1917 – World War I: The Battle of Rafa is fought near the Egyptian border with Palestine.[26]

events.description: Battle of Bear Valley: The last battle of the American Indian Wars.
events.html: • 1918 – Battle of Bear Valley: The last battle of the American Indian Wars.[27]

events.description: Ukrainian War of Independence: The All-Ukrainian Central Executive Committee outlaws the Makhnovshchina by decree, igniting the Bolshevik–Makhnovist conflict.
events.html: • 1920 – Ukrainian War of Independence: The All-Ukrainian Central Executive Committee outlaws the Makhnovshchina by decree, igniting the Bolshevik–Makhnovist conflict.[28]

events.description: Greco-Turkish War: The First Battle of İnönü, the first battle of the war, begins near Eskişehir in Anatolia.
events.html: • 1921 – Greco-Turkish War: The First Battle of İnönü, the first battle of the war, begins near Eskişehir in Anatolia.[29]

events.description: Juan de la Cierva makes the first autogyro flight.
events.html: • 1923 – Juan de la Cierva makes the first autogyro flight.[30]

events.description: Lithuanian residents of the Memel Territory rebel against the League of Nations' decision to leave the area as a mandated region under French control.
events.html: • 1923 – Lithuanian residents of the Memel Territory rebel against the League of Nations' decision to leave the area as a mandated region under French control.

events.description: A fire at the Laurier Palace movie theatre in Montreal, Quebec, Canada, kills 78 children.
events.html: • 1927 – A fire at the Laurier Palace movie theatre in Montreal, Quebec, Canada, kills 78 children.[31]

events.description: World War II: First flight of the Avro Lancaster.
events.html: • 1941 – World War II: First flight of the Avro Lancaster.[32]

events.description: World War II: The Sixth United States Army begins the invasion of Lingayen Gulf.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: The Sixth United States Army begins the invasion of Lingayen Gulf.[33]

events.description: British Prime Minister Sir Anthony Eden resigns from office following his failure to retake the Suez Canal from Egyptian sovereignty.
events.html: • 1957 – British Prime Minister Sir Anthony Eden resigns from office following his failure to retake the Suez Canal from Egyptian sovereignty.[34]

entities.name: Prime Minister of the United Kingdom

events.description: The Vega de Tera dam fails, triggering a disastrous flood that nearly destroys the town of Ribadelago and kills 144 residents.
events.html: • 1959 – The Vega de Tera dam fails, triggering a disastrous flood that nearly destroys the town of Ribadelago and kills 144 residents.[35]

events.description: President of Egypt Gamal Abdel Nasser opens construction on the Aswan Dam by detonating ten tons of dynamite to demolish twenty tons of granite on the east bank of the Nile.
events.html: • 1960 – President of Egypt Gamal Abdel Nasser opens construction on the Aswan Dam by detonating ten tons of dynamite to demolish twenty tons of granite on the east bank of the Nile.[36]

events.description: British authorities announce they have uncovered the Soviet Portland spy ring in London.
events.html: • 1961 – British authorities announce they have uncovered the Soviet Portland spy ring in London.

events.description: Apollo program: NASA announces plans to build the C-5 rocket launch vehicle, then known as the "Advanced Saturn", to carry human beings to the Moon.
events.html: • 1962 – Apollo program: NASA announces plans to build the C-5 rocket launch vehicle, then known as the "Advanced Saturn", to carry human beings to the Moon.[37]

events.description: Martyrs' Day: Several Panamanian youths try to raise the Panamanian flag in the U.S.-controlled Panama Canal Zone, leading to fighting between U.S. military and Panamanian civilians.
events.html: • 1964 – Martyrs' Day: Several Panamanian youths try to raise the Panamanian flag in the U.S.-controlled Panama Canal Zone, leading to fighting between U.S. military and Panamanian civilians.

events.description: Representatives from the United States and Iraq meet at the Geneva Peace Conference to try to find a peaceful resolution to the Iraqi invasion of Kuwait.
events.html: • 1991 – Representatives from the United States and Iraq meet at the Geneva Peace Conference to try to find a peaceful resolution to the Iraqi invasion of Kuwait.[38]

events.description: The Assembly of the Serb People in Bosnia and Herzegovina proclaims the creation of Republika Srpska, a new state within Yugoslavia.
events.html: • 1992 – The Assembly of the Serb People in Bosnia and Herzegovina proclaims the creation of Republika Srpska, a new state within Yugoslavia.

entities.name: Assembly of the Serb People in Bosnia and Herzegovina

events.description: The first discoveries of extrasolar planets are announced by astronomers Aleksander Wolszczan and Dale Frail. They discovered two planets orbiting the pulsar PSR 1257+12.
events.html: • 1992 – The first discoveries of extrasolar planets are announced by astronomers Aleksander Wolszczan and Dale Frail. They discovered two planets orbiting the pulsar PSR 1257+12.[39]

events.description: First Chechen War: Chechen separatists launch a raid against the helicopter airfield and later a civilian hospital in the city of Kizlyar in the neighboring Dagestan, which turns into a massive hostage crisis involving thousands of civilians.
events.html: • 1996 – First Chechen War: Chechen separatists launch a raid against the helicopter airfield and later a civilian hospital in the city of Kizlyar in the neighboring Dagestan, which turns into a massive hostage crisis involving thousands of civilians.

events.description: Comair Flight 3272 crashes in Raisinville Township in Monroe County, Michigan, killing 29 people.
events.html: • 1997 – Comair Flight 3272 crashes in Raisinville Township in Monroe County, Michigan, killing 29 people.[40]

events.description: TANS Perú Flight 222 crashes on approach to Chachapoyas Airport in Chachapoyas, Peru, killing 46 people.
events.html: • 2003 – TANS Perú Flight 222 crashes on approach to Chachapoyas Airport in Chachapoyas, Peru, killing 46 people.[41]

events.description: An inflatable boat carrying illegal Albanian emigrants stalls near the Karaburun Peninsula en route to Brindisi, Italy; exposure to the elements kills 28. This is the second deadliest marine disaster in Albanian history.
events.html: • 2004 – An inflatable boat carrying illegal Albanian emigrants stalls near the Karaburun Peninsula en route to Brindisi, Italy; exposure to the elements kills 28. This is the second deadliest marine disaster in Albanian history.[42]

events.description: Mahmoud Abbas wins the election to succeed Yasser Arafat as President of the Palestinian National Authority, replacing interim president Rawhi Fattouh.
events.html: • 2005 – Mahmoud Abbas wins the election to succeed Yasser Arafat as President of the Palestinian National Authority, replacing interim president Rawhi Fattouh.[43]

events.description: The Sudan People's Liberation Movement and the Government of Sudan sign the Comprehensive Peace Agreement to end the Second Sudanese Civil War.
events.html: • 2005 – The Sudan People's Liberation Movement and the Government of Sudan sign the Comprehensive Peace Agreement to end the Second Sudanese Civil War.[44]

events.description: Apple CEO Steve Jobs introduces the original iPhone at a Macworld keynote in San Francisco.
events.html: • 2007 – Apple CEO Steve Jobs introduces the original iPhone at a Macworld keynote in San Francisco.[45]

events.description: Iran Air Flight 277 crashes near Urmia in the northwest of the country, in icy conditions, killing 78 people.
events.html: • 2011 – Iran Air Flight 277 crashes near Urmia in the northwest of the country, in icy conditions, killing 78 people.[46]

events.html: • 2014 – An explosion at a Mitsubishi Materials chemical plant in Yokkaichi, Japan, kills at least five people and injures 17 others.[47]

events.description: The perpetrators of the Charlie Hebdo shooting in Paris two days earlier are both killed after a hostage situation; a second hostage situation, related to the Charlie Hebdo shooting, occurs at a Jewish market in Vincennes.
events.html: • 2015 – The perpetrators of the Charlie Hebdo shooting in Paris two days earlier are both killed after a hostage situation; a second hostage situation, related to the Charlie Hebdo shooting, occurs at a Jewish market in Vincennes.[48]
